						<summary>

						<p>This mutilated and damaged inscription is dated in <hi rend="bold">Chāḷukya-Vikrama kāla • • Chaitra 15,</hi> other details being lost. It seems to register a gift of gold made by Maṇḍaḷika Rājarasa, Perggaḍe Mārtaṇḍayya and others at the instance of <hi rend="bold">Tribhuvanamalla-Bhāgalamahādēvi,</hi> queen of <hi rend="bold">Tribhuvana[malladēva].</hi> Rājarasa is stated to be the maternal uncle <hi rend="italic">(māva)</hi> of Bhāgaladēvi.</p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
